&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive, Job Outcomes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Pursuit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pursuit is a social impact organization building the future of economic mobility in the age of AI.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For over a decade, we’ve transformed lives through immersive training programs that propel adults from low-income backgrounds - often without college degrees - into high-growth tech careers. Our graduates have already generated nearly $1 billion in lifetime wage gains. We’ve also pioneered the Pursuit Bond, an innovative outcomes-based financing model that aligns investor returns with long-term economic mobility, allowing us to scale impact in a financially sustainable way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now, as AI reshapes every industry, Pursuit is evolving into an AI-native organization. We’re training AI-native talent, embedding AI into our operations, and building scalable software to extend our impact. From grassroots partnerships to national policy, we’re not just filling jobs - we’re rethinking how economic opportunity works at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pursuit is seeking a highly driven, relationship-oriented Account Executive to help scale employer partnerships and drive successful job placements for Pursuit Builders entering new careers. Reporting to the Head of Job Outcomes, this person will own employer outreach and hiring pipelines from first conversation through successful placement, acting as a trusted external representative of Pursuit in the market.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a full-cycle sales role focused on generating new employer partnerships and driving successful hiring outcomes. The person in this role will own the sales process end-to-end — from outbound prospecting and discovery through pitch, relationship management, builder matching and preparation, and successful placement close.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role will work closely with the broader jobs and program teams, including leadership across employer partnerships. The ideal candidate is someone with a strong sales or business development background who thrives in fast-paced, high-volume environments, enjoys building relationships, is mission driven, and is motivated by ambitious goals and measurable outcomes. We would also prioritize someone who integrates AI into their workflows to increase efficacy across the sales process.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This role is heavily focused on net-new employer acquisition and outbound relationship development rather than long-term account management. It is critical to Pursuit’s mission of creating life-changing economic mobility opportunities for talented individuals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage a pipeline of employer relationships from outbound outreach through confirmed hire&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct high-volume outbound outreach and discovery conversations with hiring managers, recruiters, and talent leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pitch Pursuit Builders and communicate the value of partnering with Pursuit to prospective employers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with technical and operational buyers including Heads of Engineering, Product leaders, Talent Acquisition teams, HR leaders, and COOs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and develop opportunities for hiring partnerships and new employer relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and submit Builder candidates to open opportunities and help shepherd interview processes through close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal program teams to support candidate preparation and interview readiness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate pipeline tracking, outreach activity, and employer records across internal systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in weekly jobs team meetings, placement strategy discussions, and cross-functional collaboration&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Pursuit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pursuit is a social impact organization building the future of economic mobility in the age of AI. For over a decade, we’ve transformed lives through immersive training programs that propel adults from low-income backgrounds - often without college degrees - into high-growth tech careers. Our graduates have already generated nearly $1 billion in lifetime wage gains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, as AI reshapes every industry, Pursuit is evolving into an AI-native organization. We’re training AI-native talent, embedding AI into our operations, and building scalable software to extend our impact. From grassroots partnerships to national policy, we’re not just filling jobs—we’re rethinking how economic opportunity works at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chief of Staff&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pursuit is hiring a &lt;strong&gt;Chief of Staff to our CEO, Nick Simmons&lt;/strong&gt;, to serve as a force multiplier for the executive team. This is a senior leadership role at the center of strategy, execution, partnerships, and organizational alignment, helping translate vision into action, drive high-priority initiatives, and ensure the organization is operating cohesively toward our ambitious goals of economic transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a sharp, systems-minded operator who thrives in ambiguity, moves comfortably between strategy and execution, and brings strong judgment, presence, and follow-through. You’ll be joining Pursuit at a pivotal moment as we deepen our leadership in AI and workforce development, scale our programs, and build new products that expand economic mobility at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Chief of Staff will serve as a trusted thought partner to the CEO, a connector across teams, and an owner of complex, cross-cutting work that helps move the organization forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a strategic thought partner and trusted advisor to the CEO on organizational priorities, decisions, and key initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the CEO in internal and external meetings as appropriate, ensuring alignment, clear communication, and follow-through.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive organizational integration and alignment by leading cross-functional coordination toward shared goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead executive team meetings and leadership retreats, including agenda-setting, facilitation, decision capture, and accountability tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate strategic priorities into clear organizational roadmaps with defined milestones, owners, and timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain systems to track organizational performance, priority initiatives, and progress against goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a connector across teams, identifying opportunities for collaboration and removing operational bottlenecks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and, where appropriate, directly own the execution of high-priority strategic initiatives on behalf of the CEO and organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement in organizational processes, systems, and ways of working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and review high-stakes internal and external communications, including speeches, memos, and correspondence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion Pursuit’s values and culture, reinforcing a high-performing, mission-driven environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support organizational transparency and effective information flow to build trust and alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help manage the CEO’s time and attention, ensuring focus on the highest-impact priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support executive hiring processes, including role scoping, job description development, candidate screening, and interview coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
